# ADR-0043 — ask a live camera-mounted VLM detector (e.g. LocateAnything,
# ADR-0037) whether an object is visible in the CURRENT frame, on demand.
#
# Called by the reasoner's read-only `locate_in_view` tool dispatch
# (openral_reasoner_ros.reasoner_node._dispatch_locate_in_view). The detector
# node (openral_perception_ros.ros_image_detector_node) runs a one-shot
# open-vocabulary detection on the latest frame of the requested camera and
# returns whether the queried object is in view. Read-only: no actuation.
#
# Request:
#   query    — free-text / label naming the object to look for (e.g. "red mug").
#              Sent verbatim as the detector's open-vocabulary query.
#   camera   — optional camera selector. Empty = the detector's primary/default
#              camera; otherwise one of the detector's configured camera ids so
#              the reasoner can choose a viewpoint. NOT a hardcoded name.
#   detector — ADR-0056 — optional on-demand locator selector (rSkill id /
#              short alias, e.g. "omdet-turbo-locator" or "locateanything-3b").
#              Empty = the deployment's default locator. The reasoner routes the
#              call to /openral/perception/<detector>/locate_in_view; per-detector
#              service namespacing means several locators can co-exist and the
#              reasoner picks the model. This field is informational on the server
#              side (each node already owns one model); it is echoed back so the
#              prompt cascade records which locator answered.
#
# Response:
#   found          — true iff the detector grounded the object in the frame.
#   camera         — the camera id actually queried (echoes the resolved default).
#   detector       — the locator id that answered (echoes the request, or the
#                    node's own id when the request left it empty).
#   metadata_json  — ObjectsMetadata JSON (boxes/labels/confidence) when found;
#                    empty string when not found or no frame was available.

string query
string camera
string detector
---
bool found
string camera
string detector
string metadata_json
